<center>
<h1>Cycle Switching Rules (continued)</h1>
</center>
<h2>
cycle1: [guard1,2] Po -enum< P1 >elim- P2

<p>
cycle2: <font color=red>[guard2,1]</font> Po -enum< P3 -enum< P4 -enum< P5 >elim- P6

<p>
Similarly guard2,1 may specify if the problem set (P3, P4, P5 or P6) is empty then control is transferred to cycle1. In other words if cycle2 produces no solutions then M<sub>sis</sub> should switch to cycle1.  If P6 is non-empty then M<sub>sis</sub> halts.

